==================================
AuthenticationManager [Interface]
==================================

interface AuthenticationManager {
Authentication authenticate(Authentication authentication)
       throws AuthenticationException;
}

Uasage : Takes authenticate object
         returns a fully authenticated object (with roles/authorities)

Used in Http Basics
-------------------
BasicAuthenticationFilter uses it

Form Login
------------
UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter

manually API
------------
@Autowired
AuthenticationManager authenticationManager;

public String login(String username, String password) {

    Authentication auth = authenticationManager.authenticate(
        new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken(username, password)
    );

    // if success → generate JWT
    return "JWT_TOKEN";
}

It delegate to Authentication Providers

DaoAuthenticationProvider is default implementation of AuthenticationProvider.

DaoAuthenticationProvider is uses UserDetailsService & PasswordEncoder

======================
AuthenticationProvider
======================
public interface AuthenticationProvider {
    Authentication authenticate(Authentication authentication)
        throws AuthenticationException;

    boolean supports(Class<?> authentication);
}

AuthenticationProvider is responsible for the validating user credentails and returning and
authenticated object
It is the core component that performs authentication
Used by AuthenticationManager (delegation)

input  : Authentication Object (username +password)
Output : Authenticated object


