=======================
Securuty Context Holder
=======================
It is core static utility class in spirng secutiy that stores and provide access to the
current authenticated user information during request.

SecurityContextHolder = Global holder for Authentication (current user)

It holds SecurityContext contains Authentication Object

internally: SecontetxtHolder-> SecurityContext -> Authentication

1.getContext()
--------------
SecurityContext context = SecurityContextHolder.getContext();

return current SecurityContext
Never returns null (creates one if not present)


2.setContext(SecurityContext context):
-------------------------------------
SecurityContextHolder.setContext(context)

set the context manually
used in custom authentication flows

3.clearContext()
--------------
SecurityContextHolder.clearContext();

clear authentication info
used during log out

4.createEmptyContext()
  ---------------------
  SecurityContext context = SecurityContextHolder.createEmptyContext();

  create a new empty context
  Useful for manual authentication setup.

getConetextHolderStrategy()
----------------------------
SecurityContext context = SecurityContextHolder.createEmptyContext();

return internal storage strategy

Strategy Patterns inside
-------------------------
MODE_THREADLOCAL(default) ->   one context per Thread

MODE_INHERITABLETHREADLOCAL -> Child threads inherit parent context

MODE_GLOBAL -> Single global context (rarely used)

===============
Secuiry Context
===============
It is core spring security object that holds the current user's authentication
information for a request.

SecurityContext = container that stores Authentication (current user details)

strcture
----------
SecurityContextHolder
        ↓
   SecurityContext
        ↓
   Authentication
        ↓
   User + Roles

public interface SecurityContext {

    Authentication getAuthentication();

    void setAuthentication(Authentication authentication);
}

